{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T03:38:12.148Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the Claude API documentation and best practices for reasoning models, here's an explanation of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompting Thinking Models"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompting Thinking Models"},{"type":"text","text":" refers to the specialized techniques for effectively prompting Claude's reasoning-capable models (like Claude Opus 4.6, Claude Sonnet 4.6) that use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"adaptive thinking"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"thinking: {type: \"adaptive\"}"},{"type":"text","text":"). These models perform internal reasoning before responding, similar to how a human would \"think through\" a complex problem."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Thinking models behave fundamentally differently from standard GPT-style models:\n- They "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"think longer and harder"},{"type":"text","text":" on complex tasks, making them effective at strategizing and planning\n- They handle "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ambiguous information"},{"type":"text","text":" better and often ask clarifying questions instead of guessing\n- The quality of your prompt matters "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"significantly more"},{"type":"text","text":" than with non-reasoning models"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without proper prompting techniques, you risk "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"overthinking"},{"type":"text","text":" (excessive token usage, latency) or getting suboptimal reasoning."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Benefits"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Better complex problem-solving"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Works through ambiguity and multi-step reasoning"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Higher accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"More reliable decision-making for math, science, engineering, legal"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle large context"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent at finding relationships across hundreds of pages"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"a